    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-04T18:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-04T18:36:00-05:00" n="231"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.51/287: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-04T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received May 6, 12.45 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s April 23rd, 6 p.m. …</p>
                <p>Mr. Catlin has not entered deeply into the subject of the loan as he is
                    endeavoring to make his services on that project conditional on acquisition
                    electric company on favorable conditions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
